de.wwu.muggl.ui.easy
Class EasyWrapper

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Thread
      de.wwu.muggl.ui.easy.EasyWrapper
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public final class EasyWrapper
extends java.lang.Thread

The EasyWrapper is an interface for the EASy system but could also be used by other third party tools. It is initialized with a class file and the name of the method. This method can be executed with Muggl, resulting in the generation of a JUnit test case file. The content of this file can be retrieved.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-12-08
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

Initialize the wrapper.

Be sure to use cleanUp() when you do not need this object any more.

Parameters:

maximumExecutionTime - Maximum execution time in seconds. -1 disables it.

wasSuccessful

public boolean wasSuccessful()
Check whether execution was successful.

Further information about why execution failed might be available from the log file. However, debugging will be almost impossible using this wrapper only. Please contact the Muggl author.

Returns:
true, if execution is finished and was successful; false otherwise.

cleanUp

public void cleanUp()
Clean up Muggl. Using this method is recommended to clean up Muggl's memory footprint. It will eventually be cleaned by the garbage collector. This could however take a while due to the complexity of the structures created. Moreover, execution might use very much memory; cleaning it up speeds up further processing.
